TUNIS, Oct. 20 (Xinhua) -- Tunisian Minister of Foreign Affairs Othman Jerandi received on Wednesday the visiting Acting Assistant Secretary of the United State Department's Bureau of Near Eastern Affairs, Yael Lempert, and discussed the situation in Tunisia. According to a statement released by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Jerandi stressed during the meeting that the formation of the new government "is the first important step that indicates the president's response to the aspirations of the people." Jerandi also said that Tunisian President Kais Saied will announce the continuation of the exceptional measures which would reassure Tunisia's partners abroad, stressing the importance of their support. For her part, the U.S. official underlined the importance and solidity of Tunisian-U.S. relations, expressing her country's willingness to continue to support Tunisia in facing various challenges and support its development programs and structural reforms. Enditem